-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">f.</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">Ensuring that appointments panels and committees have female representation (we do not impose a particul</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">ar percentage to avoid adversel</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">y</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">impacting on women’s time commitment to such activities)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">g.</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">Increasing visibility of senior academic women via seminar speakers, chairing responsibilities, and a regular school-wide newsletter</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">h.</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">Ensuring that women are as well supported as men in promot</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">ions processes.</span></p><p style="margin:0.1pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0.1pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0.1pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Times; font-s